title: Iria: Volume II
author: Gobblin
pages:
#- Civcraft: Iria§0
§0-------------------A complete history -§0
§0VOLUME 2§0.§0
§0-------------------§0
§0POST CORUM:§0
§0Despite losing all its allies and trading partners, Iria soldiered on, and actually did quite well for a period. It's population grew, 
#- and the nearby town of Kilfordshire was annexed to allow for expansion. DiamondReaper built the Diamond Hotel to house new friends, IHOP007 built a sewer system that remained for years to come, u5ggg built a bumper boat pool, Lottosprayer 
#- began building a gigantic cathedral that was set to be one of the biggest builds on the server. 5365616e lead an effort to build a version of Iria in the End but it was griefed after one day. However the prosperity of Iria ended up coming to an end as 
#- Lottosprayer quit without notice of explanation. This plunged the town into chaos as he was the sole admin of a few citadel groups, and he was half way through building his cathedral. He left behind him a 'hulking, unfinished reinforced eyesore' that was 
#- larger than Iria itself. It was also described as 'a depressing influenced that overshadowed the town and any progress we tried to make'. It bcame out Ryugyong Hotel. In the aftermath of Lotto's disappearance, a council was formed of H
#- Horizon, 3earGryllis, 5365616e, Sloths_Rock and wolfeyes391. The council proved to be ineffective.§0
§0
§0ZASHGEO INCIDENT:§0
§0Two irian citizens, Zash and Geo were charged with treason and vaulted after a 'prank' where they pearled citizens
#- and left town with the pearls. While some still feel their actions were out of line, people think that the anger of the previous events was channeled towards them, effecting their trial. Irians ending up inside the Irian vault was an 'end of innocence' 
#- for the once carefree town.§0
§0
§0INF INVASION: Iria slipped into further isolation as Bryn and Fellowship went inactive. The town was now more alone, and evem more at the mercy of raiders. Iria was raided and then occupied by INF raiders
#- for a number of days. Nobody came to help the town, other than a bounty hunter named DosEquisMan. the town folk co-ordinated resistance efforts with DosEquisMan however they always seemed to fail, and DosEquisMan continuously refused 
#- to 'actually fight' the INF. At first, wolfeyes391 thought that DosEquisMan was really just an a incompetent bounty hunter, but then he became suspicious. He informed DosEquisMan of a rendezvous point where he direced a few citizens to meet up - who were 
#- promptly pearled by INF members waiting for them. It turned out that DosEquisMan was no bounty hunter, but instead an undercover INF mole who had been informing them of Irian plans for the entire time. For a few days, wolfeyes391 Sloths_Rock and u5ggg
#- attempted to organised another resistance movement headquartered in the basement of the old kilfordshire Mayor's mansion, but to no success. With it's wealth stolen, factories broken, allies long gone, houses filled with privately
#- reinforced melons (courtesy of KillYourFaceGo), and the town at the mercy of hostiles, Civcraft was described as 'simply not fun anymore', by Irians.§0
§0
§0THE WILDERNESS YEARS:§0
§0By the end of 2013, most irians had quit the server entiretly but a few stalwarts,
#- wolfeyes391, eatsnails3, Sloths_Rock and u5ggg ventured to other towns. The land stood silent for some time except when it was distrubed by an occasional traveler or two. eventually, two people from the nearby newly froemd settlement of Falcon
#- Crest thought Iria was fully abandoned as opposed to 'dormant', and decided to come pillage what was left. Skywatch was founded to the south of Iria, and then died as well, joining a number of ruins in close proximitty to Iria, many of which were left 
#- nameless. The Curse of the Corum Region lived on.§0
§0
§0THE REVIVAL OF IRIA:§0
§0In january 2014, 3 events acted to revive the nation of Iria.§0
§0
§0*Zash and an explorer, Krist, started the 
#- 'Iria Restoration Commitiee'. While others ended up doing most of the actual restoration, they encouraged others to be more active and got the ball rolling again.§0
§0
§0*Lottosprayer made a shocking reappearance, and finally tore down his
#- cathedral and finished it on a much smaller plot of land.§0
§0
§0*With Fellowship and Bryn revived, and Saraliana founded north, and a rail built right under the town. Iria was no longer isolated, and for the first time in many months
#- had potential allies and trade partners within a reasonable distance.§0
§0
§0A large amount of old Iria was demolished to allow for new developments and a new town plan. New work was started and new projects made,
#- but there were some minor conflicts in this peiod.§0
§0
§0-Fellowship claimed Iria, which Horizon and other Irians objected on the grounds that Iria was never fully abandonded. Nico came to Iria and made some undiplomatic comments that inflamed the situation
#- but an agreement was eventually reached in Mumble.§0
§0
§0-An irian resident, Arcane, pillaged from Falcon Crest thinking it was abandoned, when it wasn't. A Falcon Crest resident was given permission by Wolfeyes to pearl Arcane on Irian soil if he refused to
#- return the items or pay reps. Arcane dnied his actions and ended up getting pearled, and then got people from Fellowship to pearl his pearler, who did not appreciate getting pearled and put on trial (which he refused to participate in). Falcon Crest would
#- later be peacefullly annexed by Iria, when its original founded, Syril, agreed for it to become part of Iria.
#- 